parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to lock up or offer high resistance, making it difficult to turn, especially during cold starts, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel locks up
high resistance when turning
especially to the right
difficulty turning at any degree greater than a lane change
intermittent steering wheel lock-up when started.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear load leveling system can cause the rear of the vehicle to bottom out, affecting its stability and handling, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The rear of the vehicle bottoms out
even with minimal load
affecting its stability and handling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headliner can cause it to hang down, obstructing the driver's view and creating a distraction, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The headliner comes loose and hangs down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cassette player can cause it to malfunction, creating a distraction for the driver, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The cassette player plays for a few seconds and then ejects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine sputtering and misfires can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, affecting its performance and safety, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The engine sputters and misfires
even after replacing tune-up related items.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brake hose can cause the brakes to lock up or malfunction, affecting the vehicle's stopping ability, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The front brake hose clogs and locks the brake
causing the vehicle to pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle may accelerate rapidly without the driver's input.
symptoms: The engine races uncontrollably
the vehicle accelerates rapidly without the driver's input
the brakes do not hold
the vehicle moves on its own
the vehicle accelerates in an unexpected manner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control failure can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, as the vehicle may continue to accelerate without the driver's input.
symptoms: The cruise control does not disengage
the vehicle accelerates rapidly without the driver's input
the cruise control nylon bushing fails
the vehicle moves on its own.
